def: A thick loose woolen jacket, or coat, much worn by sailors incold weather.
The act or practice of hunting or shooting game with a gun.The art of gunning was but little practiced. Goldsmith.
Distinguished bravery; valor; especially, military bravery andskill; gallantry; intrepidity; fearlessness. Chaucer. Sir P. Sidney.He by his prowess conquered all France. Shak.
Full of daisies; adorned with daisies. "The daisied green."Langhorne.The grass all deep and daisied. G. Eliot.
That which takes up or tightens; specifically, a device in asewing machine for drawing up the slack thread as the needle rises,in completing a stitch.
The state of being recusant; nonconformity. Coke.
Closely examining, or inquiring; careful; sctrict.-- Scru"ti*nous*ly, adv.
